<br>
In any case since this isn’t an Equipment Check post/forum I won’t link my Magelo profile here (I’m still working on it anyway). But this AC discussion did bring up two questions:<br>
<br>
There are two pieces of armor I’ve been thinking of replacing with better stats armor after I buy my FBSS (1.5K more to go (4K on my server)):<br>
<br>
Deepwater Gauntlets – Gauntlets of the Black<br>
<br>
Greaves of Ro – Crustacean Greaves<br>
<br>
As a Half-Elf I NEED stamina, and the STR/WIS on the Gauntlets would be nice (and needed now that my Helm of Ro has been replaced with DW). So my question is this, I lose 1 AC on each of these items but gain stats that I definitely need. Should I go for this? I’m not going to ask for further suggestions because as I said, I’m just wondering if the above is a good example of “give a little AC and get back good stats.” Thanks.<br>
<br>
Tramaus Voronadil<br>
